  "data": "{
  "query": "\"Non-Spinning Reserve Service\" \"Additional Operational Details\" ERCOT ramping sustain",
  "num_results": 8,
  "results": [
    {
      "url": "https://www.ercot.com/services/comm/mkt_notices/detail?id=1ed6d29b-e8df-41b5-9f26-ee491fe2ef6d",
      "title": "Market Notice Details",
      "text": "Market Notice Details\n\nTo: Notice_PRR_SCR@lists.ercot.com,Notice_Settlements@lists.ercot.com,NOTICE_GENERAL@LISTS.ERCOT.COM,Notice_Operations@lists.ercot.com,Notice_Release_Retail@lists.ercot.com,Notice_Release_Wholesale@lists.ercot.com\n\nSent: 5/13/22, 9:36 AM\n\nSubject: M-A042222-02 Implementation Details of NPRR1093, NPRR1101, OBDRR032, OBDRR033, and OBDRR035\n\n---\n\nNOTICE DATE: May 13, 2022\n\nNOTICE TYPE: M-A042222-02 NPRR\n\nSHORT DESCRIPTION: Implementation Details of NPRR1093, NPRR1101, OBDRR032, OBDRR033, and OBDRR035\n\nINTENDED AUDIENCE: All Market Participants\n\nDAYS AFFECTED: May 27, 2022\n\nLONG DESCRIPTION: On May 27, 2022, Protocol and Other Binding Document language associated with the following Revision Requests will be implemented:\n\n- OBDRR035, Non-Spin Changes Related to NPRR1101\n- OBDRR033, ORDC Changes Related to NPRR1093; and\n- Other Binding Document Revision Request (OBDRR) 032, Non-Spin Changes Related to NPRR1093;\n- NPRR1101, Create Non-Spin Deployment Groups made up of Generation Resources Providing Off-Line Non-Spinning Reserve and Load Resources that are Not Controllable Load Resources Providing Non-Spinning Reserve;\n- Nodal Protocol Revision Request (NPRR) 1093, Load Resource Participation in Non-Spinning Reserve;\n\nThe combination of the above Revision Requests allow for Non-Spinning Reserve (Non-Spin) provision from Load Resources that are not Controllable Load Resources and defines how Resources providing Non-Spin are grouped and deployed.\n\nTechnical specifications of the changes to ERCOT interfaces as a result of this effort were shared at the February 10, 2022 Technology Working Group meeting. ERCOT also hosted an April 25, 2022 workshop to provide additional details on this effort.\n\nERCOT Market Operations Test Environment (MOTE) is available for Market Participants to voluntarily test submission functions related to NPRR1093, which began May 5, 2022.\n\nNPRR1093 introduces the following changes to the Settlement System:\n\n- Protocol Section 6.7.5, Real-Time Ancillary Service Imbalance Payment or Charge – Updates Online Imbalance and Offline Imbalance calculations to account for Load Resources that are not Controllable Load Resources participating in Non-Spin Reserve.\n\nNew Settlement Billing Determinants:\n\nBilling Determinant\n\nShort Description\n\nExtract\n\nExtract Table\n\nRTNCLRNSRESPR\n\nReal-Time Non-Controllable Load Resource Non-Spin Responsibility for the Resource\n\nSID & RTM CODE\n\nMKTINPUTHEADER\n\nMKTINPUTINTERVAL\n\nRTNCLRNSRESP\n\nReal-Time Non-Controllable Load Resource Non-Spin Responsibility for the QSE\n\nRTM CODE\n\nRTMOUTPUTHEADER\n\nRTMOUTPUTINTERVAL\n\nRTNCLRNSR\n\nReal-Time Non-Spin Schedule for the Non-Controllable Load Resource\n\nSID & RTM CODE\n\nMKTINPUTHEADER\n\nMKTINPUTINTERVAL\n\nRTNCLRNS\n\nReal-Time Non-Spin Schedule for the Non-Controllable Load Resources for the QSE\n\nRTM CODE\n\nRTMOUTPUTHEADER\n\nRTMOUTPUTINTERVAL\n\nRTNCLRNSCAP\n\nReal-Time Capacity from Non-Controllable Load Resources Carrying Non-Spin for the QSE\n\nRTM CODE\n\nRTMOUTPUTHEADER\n\nRTMOUTPUTINTERVAL\n\nAdditionally, there will be several reporting changes introduced with the implementation of NPRR1093. Please note that changes to disclosure reports will occur post implementation and align to the applicable operating days affected.\n\nThe following new Certified reports will need to be added to the EMIL and MIS:\n\n1) Monthly Non-Spin NCLR Performance Report | NP8-385-ER | Report Type ID 220692) Group Assignments for NCLRs and Off-Line Generation Resources Participating in NSRS | NP6-577-CD | Report Type ID 21939\n\nThe following two reports will have a column added for ‘RTNCLRNSCAP’:\n\n1) Real-Time ORDC and Reliability Deployment Price Adders and Reserves by SCED Interval |NP6-323-CD| Report Type ID 13221\n\n2) Historical Real Time ORDC and Reliability Deployment Price Adders and Reserves |NP6-792-ER| Report Type ID 13231\n\nThe following reports will be modified for the NSPIN Column to be split out to account for new subtype of NSPNM:\n\n1) 60D SCED Disclosure Report | NP3-965-ER | Report Type ID 13052Output file: Output file: 60-Day QSE-Specific Self-Arranged AS in SCED\n\n2) 60D DAM Disclosure Report | NP3-966-ER | Report Type ID 13051Output file: Output file: 60-Day QSE-Specific Self-Arranged AS in DAM\n\nLastly, a new output file will be added within the zipfile for 2-Day Ancillary Services Disclosure |NP3-911-ER | Report Type ID 13057\n\nAS ‘2d_Self_Arranged_AS_NSPNM’ due to new NSPNM subtype\n\nACTION REQUIRED: Impacted Market Participants should implement changes to their shadow Settlement systems to incorporate the revisions made by NPRR1093, NPRR1101, OBDRR032, OBDRR033, and OBDRR035.\n\nADDITIONAL INFORMATION: Pursuant to Nodal Protocol Section 21.6, Nodal Protocol Revision Implementation, ERCOT is required to provide notice as soon as practicable, but no later than ten days prior to implementation.\n\nNPRR1093, NPRR1101, OBDRR032, OBDRR033, OBDRR035 and their associated documents can be found on the ERCOT website.\n\nAdditional Settlement details can be found in the Settlements Charge Matrix located on the Settlements page on ERCOT.com.\n\nResource Entities and Qualified Scheduling Entities (QSEs) representing Load Resources that are interested in providing Non-Spin pursuant to the changes in this effort are encouraged to review the meeting materials from the April 25, 2022 workshop.\n\nCONTACT: If you have any questions, please contact your ERCOT Account Manager. You may also call the general ERCOT Client Services phone number at (512) 248-3900 or contact ERCOT Client Services via email at ClientServices@ercot.com.\n\nIf you are receiving email from a public ERCOT distribution list that you no longer wish to receive, please follow this link in order to unsubscribe from this list: http://lists.ercot.com.\n\ndg",
      "highlights": [
        "- OBDRR035, Non-Spin Changes Related to NPRR1101\n- OBDRR033, ORDC Changes Related to NPRR1093; and\n- Other Binding Document Revision Request (OBDRR) 032, Non-Spin Changes Related to NPRR1093;\n- NPRR1101, Create Non-Spin Deployment Groups made up of Generation Resources Providing Off-Line Non-Spinning Reserve and Load Resources that are Not Controllable Load Resources Providing Non-Spinning Reserve;\n- Nodal Protocol Revision Request (NPRR) 1093, Load Resource Participation in Non-Spinning Reserve;\n[...]\nThe combination of the above Revision Requests allow for Non-Spinning Reserve (Non-Spin) provision from Load Resources that are not Controllable Load Resources and defines how Resources providing Non-Spin are grouped and deployed.\n[...]\nTechnical specifications of the changes to ERCOT interfaces as a result of this effort were shared at the February 10, 2022 Technology Working Group meeting. ERCOT also hosted an April 25, 2022 workshop to provide additional details on this effort.\n[...]\n- Protocol Section 6.7.5, Real-Time Ancillary Service Imbalance Payment or Charge – Updates Online Imbalance and Offline Imbalance calculations to account for Load Resources that are not Controllable Load Resources participating in Non-Spin Reserve.\n[...]\n, there will be\n[...]\nreporting changes introduced with the implementation of NPRR1093\n[...]\nPlease note that\n[...]\napplicable operating days affected.\n[...]\nACTION REQUIRED: Impacted Market Participants should implement changes to their shadow Settlement systems to incorporate the revisions made by NPRR1093, NPRR1101, OBDRR032, OBDRR033, and OBDRR035.\n[...]\nERCOT is\n[...]\nto provide notice as soon as practicable, but no later than ten days prior to implementation.\n[...]\nResource Entities and Qualified Scheduling Entities (QSEs) representing Load Resources that are interested in providing Non-Spin pursuant to the changes in this effort are encouraged to review the meeting materials from the April 25, 2022 workshop."
      ]
    },
