      "text": "Issues\n\n- Home\n- Market Rules\n- Issues\n\n## NPRR532\n\n- Summary\n- Action\n- Voting Record\n- Background\n- Key Documents\n\n#### Summary\n\n06/01/2014\n\n| Title | Performance Measurement and Verification and Telemetry Requirements for Load Resources Providing Non-Spin |\n| --- | --- |\n| Next Group |\n| Next Step |\n| Status | Approved on 09/17/2013 |\n| Effective Dates |\n\n#### Action\n\n| Date | Gov Body | Action Taken | Next Steps |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| 09/17/2013 | BOARD | Approved |\n| 09/05/2013 | TAC | Recommended for Approval | ERCOT Board consideration of NPRR532 |\n| 08/22/2013 | PRS | PRS consideration of NPRR532 |\n| 07/18/2013 | PRS | Deferred/Tabled | PRS Impact Analysis review |\n| 06/20/2013 | PRS | Recommended for Approval | PRS Impact Analysis review |\n| 04/18/2013 | PRS | Deferred/Tabled | PRS language consideration |\n\n#### Voting Record\n\n| Date | Gov Body | Motion | Result |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| 09/17/2013 | BOARD | To approve NPRR532 as recommended by TAC in the 9/5/13 TAC Report. | Passed |\n| 09/05/2013 | TAC | To recommend approval of NPRR532 as recommended by PRS in the 8/22/13 PRS Report and as amended by the 8/29/13 ERCOT comments. | Passed |\n| 08/22/2013 | PRS | to grant NPRR532 Urgent status | Passed |\n| 07/18/2013 | PRS | To table NPRR532 for one month. | Passed |\n| 06/20/2013 | PRS | To recommend approval of NPRR532 as amended by the 6/18/13 Citigroup Energy comments. | Passed |\n| 04/18/2013 | PRS | To table NPRR532 and refer the issue to WMS and ROS. | Passed |\n\n#### Background\n\n| Status: | Approved |\n| --- | --- |\n| Date Posted: | Mar 26, 2013 |\n| Sponsor: | DSWG |\n| Urgent: | Yes |\n| Sections: | 3.9.1, 4.4.7.2.1, 6.5.5.2, 6.5.7.6.2.3, 8.1.1.2.1.3, 8.1.1.3.3, 8.1.1.4.3 |\n| Description: | This Nodal Protocol Revision Request (NPRR) enables participation in the Non-Spinning Reserve (Non-Spin) Service market for Load Resources whose provision of Demand response is most accurately measured and verified using a baseline performance evaluation methodology. The NPRR establishes a method for evaluating Non-Spin performance using a baseline methodology, which compares actual Load to a reliable estimate of what the Load would have been in the absence of the deployment. This NPRR also establishes new telemetry requirements for Qualified Scheduling Entities (QSEs) representing Load Resources in the Non-Spin market to allow ERCOT’s systems to monitor the status and performance of those Load Resources in Real-Time. |\n| Reason: | Current market rules relating to Load Resource performance evaluation in Ancillary Services are limited to a methodology best described as \"meter-before/meter-after\" (as defined in North American Energy Standards Board (NAESB) Demand Response Measurement & Verification standards, adopted by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission (FERC)). Under this existing methodology, a Load reduction in a deployment event is measured from the Load Resource&rsquo;s static Load level at the time of Dispatch; the Load Resource must maintain such reduction throughout the event. This works well for industrial consumers with high Load factors, but can lead to either over-provision or under-provision of Demand response by other types of consumers, especially weather-sensitive Loads. NAESB and FERC standards also provide for the baseline methodology, which measures and verifies performance by comparing actual Load to a reliable estimate of what the Load would have been in the absence of the deployment. |\n\n#### Key Documents\n\n532NPRR-01 Performance Measurement and Verification and Telemetr\n\nMar 26, 2013 - doc - 110 KB\n\n532NPRR-02 PRS Report 041813\n\nApr 22, 2013 - doc - 110 KB\n\n532NPRR-03 WMS Comments 050913\n\nMay 9, 2013 - doc - 39.5 KB\n\n532NPRR-04 Edison Mission Marketing & Trading Comments 061313\n\nJun 13, 2013 - doc - 45.5 KB\n\n532NPRR-05 WMS Comments 061413\n\nJun 14, 2013 - doc - 39.5 KB\n\n532NPRR-06 ROS Comments 061713\n\nJun 17, 2013 - doc - 48.5 KB\n\n532NPRR-07 ROS Voting Ballot 061713\n\nJun 17, 2013 - xls - 130 KB\n\n532NPRR-08 Citigroup Energy Comments 061813\n\nJun 21, 2013 - doc - 110 KB\n\n532NPRR-09 PRS Report 062013\n\nJun 24, 2013 - doc - 134 KB\n\n532NPRR-10 ERCOT Comments 071813\n\nJul 18, 2013 - doc - 39.5 KB\n\n532NPRR-11 PRS Report 071813\n\nJul 22, 2013 - doc - 136.5 KB\n\n532NPRR-12 WMS Comments 081913\n\nAug 19, 2013 - doc - 44 KB\n\n532NPRR-13 Impact Analysis 081913\n\nAug 19, 2013 - doc - 57 KB\n\n532NPRR-14 PRS Report 082213\n\nAug 26, 2013 - doc - 146.5 KB\n\n532NPRR-15 ERCOT Comments 082913\n\nAug 29, 2013 - doc - 102.5 KB\n\n532NPRR-17 TAC Report 090513\n\nSep 5, 2013 - doc - 150.5 KB\n\n532NPRR-18 Board Report 091713\n\nSep 18, 2013 - doc - 152 KB\n\n##### Related Content\n\n###### On this site",
