      "text": "Issues\n\n- Home\n- Market Rules\n- Issues\n\n## NPRR332\n\n- Summary\n- Action\n- Voting Record\n- Background\n- Key Documents\n\n#### Summary\n\n08/01/2011\n\n| Title | Revise QSGR Processes for COP Reporting of QSGR Assigned Off-Line Non-Spin and Application of Emergency Operations Settlement |\n| --- | --- |\n| Next Group |\n| Next Step |\n| Status | Approved on 07/19/2011 |\n| Effective Dates |\n\n#### Action\n\n| Date | Gov Body | Action Taken | Next Steps |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| 07/19/2011 | BOARD | Approved |\n| 06/02/2011 | TAC | Recommended for Approval | ERCOT Board consideration of NPRR332 |\n| 05/19/2011 | PRS | Recommended for Approval | TAC consideration of NPRR332 |\n| 04/21/2011 | PRS | Recommended for Approval | PRS Impact Analysis review |\n| 03/24/2011 | PRS | Referred | WMS consideration of NPRR332 |\n\n#### Voting Record\n\n| Date | Gov Body | Motion | Result |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| 07/19/2011 | BOARD | To approve NPRR332 as recommended by TAC in the 6/2/11 TAC Report. | Passed |\n| 06/02/2011 | TAC | To recommend approval of NPRR332 as recommended by PRS in the 5/19/11 PRS Report and as revised by TAC. | Passed |\n| 05/19/2011 | PRS | To endorse and forward the 4/21/11 PRS Report and Impact Analysis for NPRR332 to TAC. | Passed |\n| 04/21/2011 | PRS | To recommend approval of NPRR332 as amended by the 4/11/11 WMS comments and to instruct WMS to evaluate the implications of using Non-Spin Service in the manner envisioned by NPRR272, Definition and Participation of Quick Start Generation Resources. | Passed |\n| 03/24/2011 | PRS | To refer NPRR332 to WMS. | Passed |\n\n#### Background\n\n| Status: | Approved |\n| --- | --- |\n| Date Posted: | Feb 25, 2011 |\n| Sponsor: | ERCOT |\n| Urgent: | No |\n| Sections: | 3.8.3, 3.9.1, 6.4.6, 6.6.9 |\n| Description: | This Nodal Protocol Revision Request (NPRR): Clarifies the COP reporting requirements for a Quick Start Generation Resource (QSGR) that is providing Off-Line Non-Spinning Reserve (Non--Spin) Service in an amount that is greater than High Sustained Limit (HSL) minus Low Sustained Limit (LSL); and Removes the requirement for a Qualified Scheduling Entity (QSE) to contact the ERCOT Operator to request a \"manual override\" when a QSGR it represents is first deployed by Security-Constrained Economic Dispatch (SCED) from a zero Base Point to a Base Point that is less than the QSGR’s physical LSL. Emergency operations Settlement provisions for QSGR deployments by SCED will be managed internally by ERCOT. |\n| Reason: | The process changes included in this NPRR: Clarify the QSE’s responsibilities in regard to its QSGR Resources that are providing Off-Line Non-Spin; and Reduce the communications demands placed on the QSE and ERCOT Operators to accommodate the application of the emergency operations Settlement provisions. |\n\n#### Key Documents\n\n332NPRR-01 Revise QSGR Processes for COP Reporting of QSGR Assig\n\nFeb 25, 2011 - doc - 111 KB\n\n332NPRR-02 Impact Analysis 022511\n\nFeb 25, 2011 - doc - 43.5 KB\n\n332NPRR-03 Revised Impact Analysis 030411\n\nMar 4, 2011 - doc - 54.5 KB\n\n332NPRR-04 PRS Report 032411\n\nMar 28, 2011 - doc - 114.5 KB\n\n332NPRR-05 WMS Comments 041111\n\nApr 11, 2011 - doc - 73.5 KB\n\n332NPRR-06 PRS Report 042111\n\nApr 26, 2011 - doc - 117.5 KB\n\n332NPRR-07 PRS Report 051911\n\nMay 20, 2011 - doc - 118 KB\n\n332NPRR-08 TAC Report 060211\n\nJun 3, 2011 - doc - 121 KB\n\n332NPRR-09 Board Report 071911\n\nJul 19, 2011 - doc - 121.5 KB\n\n##### Related Content\n\n###### On this site",
